'''Great Eppleton Wind Farm''' is a [[wind farm]] near [[Hetton-le-Hole]], [[England]]. It is owned and operated by [[E.ON UK]]. Constructed in 1997, it was notable for originally consisting of twin-bladed turbines, as most [[wind turbine]]s have three blades. On 29 September 2009 E.ON announced it would replace these with four new [[REpower]] MM92 turbines giving a [[Intermittent energy source#Terminology|nameplate capacity]] of 8.2 [[Megawatt|MW]].<ref>http://www.newenergyfocus.com/do/ecco/view_item?listid=1&listcatid=131&listitemid=3048</ref><ref>{{Cite web | url=http://www.bwea.com/ukwed/operational.asp | title=UKWED Operational wind farms | publisher=[[RenewableUK]] | accessdate=2009-11-13 | deadurl=yes | archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121102132011/http://www.bwea.com/ukwed/operational.asp | archivedate=2012-11-02 | df= }}</ref><ref>{{cite news| url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/1/hi/england/wear/6249325.stm | work=BBC News | title=Wind farm upgrade plan revealed | date=10 January 2007 | accessdate=4 May 2010}}</ref>
