{{Infobox protected area | name = Palmiet Nature Reserve | alt_name = | iucn_category = | photo = | photo_width = | photo_alt = | photo_caption = | map = South Africa KwaZulu-Natal | map_alt = | map_caption = Map of [[KwaZulu-Natal]] | map_width = | relief = 1 | location = [[Durban]], [[South Africa]] | coordinates = {{coord|29.820423|S|30.9314459|E|region:ZA-NL|format=dms|display=inline,title}} | coords_ref = | area = {{Convert|90|ha|abbr=on}} | established = 1972 | visitation_num = | visitation_year = | governing_body = [[Ethekwini Metropolitan Municipality]] | url = }}
'''Palmiet Nature Reserve''' is located in [[Westville, KwaZulu-Natal|Westville]], a town located ten kilometres from [[Durban]], [[South Africa]]. The reserve is made up of a wide variety of natural habitats ranging from forests to grassland.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://showme.co.za/durban/lifestyle/palmiet-nature-reserve/|title=Palmiet Nature Reserve {{!}} Durban|website=showme.co.za|access-date=2016-07-07}}</ref> Hundreds of bird species have been recorded<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.palmiet.za.net/birds.htm|title=Palmiet Nature Reserve Birds|website=www.palmiet.za.net}}</ref> and the tree list is extensive. There are a number of self-guided trails that include river crossings.<ref name=":0">{{Cite web|url=http://www.sa-venues.com/game-reserves/kzn_palmiet.htm|title=Palmiet Nature Reserve|website=www.sa-venues.com|access-date=2016-07-07}}</ref>
Igwalagwala Cliff, found in the reserve, is a site of archaeological significance as it has evidence of prehistoric human habitation.<ref name=":0" />
