'''Surface Water Improvement and Management Program''' ('''S.W.I.M''', sometimes written as '''SWIM''') is a [[Florida]] [[Government of Florida|state program]] to improve Florida's [[water quality]].<ref>[http://www.dep.state.fl.us/water/watersheds/swim.htm]<sup> (needs authentication)</sup></ref>

== History ==
Swim was started in 1988 by the [[Florida Department of Environmental Protection|Department of Environmental Protection]] to address Florida's worsening water quality and protect [[drinking water]] quality.

